com.noctarius.tengi.core.serialization.debugger

Interface DebuggableMarshaller<O>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of the written and read object
    All Superinterfaces:
    Marshaller<O>, MarshallerReader<O>, MarshallerWriter<O>

    public interface DebuggableMarshaller<O>
extends Marshaller<O>
    The DebuggableMarshaller is a special type of Marshaller that is able to identify types in a byte-stream before the actual deserialization happens.

    • Method Detail

      • findType

        Class<?> findType(Decoder decoder,
                  Protocol protocol)

        Returns the real type of the next object in the stream which can be the simple type for Marshaller implementations that handle just one type or it can read additional information from the stream to gather necessary type information.

        If additional read operations are executed, the stream is automatically reset to the position before calling this method. No additional preparation is necessary.

        Parameters:
        decoder - the Decoder to read from
        protocol - the Protocol instance for additional protocol complexity
        Returns:
        the type of the next object in the stream

      • debugValue

        String debugValue(Object value)
        Returns the debug value of the given object. This debug value is normally a shrunk down version of the actual content of the value.
        Parameters:
        value - the value to turn into a debug value
        Returns:
        the debug value of the given object
